- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses differential privacy, which is a concept from information theory, to ensure privacy of the input data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses the dual multiplicative weight update (DMWU) algorithm, which is a popular algorithm in machine learning, to solve the packing problem. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses the hardness of the packing problem and provides a lower bound on the supply of each resource required for any differentially private algorithm to compute an approximately optimal packing solution, which is a concept from game theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of the packing problem and presents an algorithm that runs in linear time, which is a concept from computational complexity.
